def: A cross, set upon three steps; -- more properly called crosscalvary.
Of or pertaining to a parish; restricted to a parish; as,parochial duties. "Parochial pastors." Bp. Atterbury. Hence, limited;narrow. "The parochial mind." W. Black.
Not conversant; not acquainted; not versed; unfamiliar.
To revile or abuse in scurrilous language. Southey.
Exhausted of moisture; parched with heat; dry; barren. "An aridwaste." Thomson.
A rope with a hook and a toggle, sometimes used to drag a guncarriage or to lash it to the limber, and for various other purposes.
Of or pertaining to a repast, especially to dinner.
